$interpreted: Cecil: The quality of the Capitol's hunting party has dropped quite a bit. I can't believe a low-class doorman has found his way into the party.
Cecil: If you can't find a seat, I suggest you go stand next to the door.
Jahan: My, my, what's wrong with noble education these days? Such vulgar and impolite words.
Jahan: If the party consists of people like this, I would rather stay outside.
Cecil: What did you just say!
Jahan: Ah, isn't this the Vincent family's young master? Judging from his speech, I thought it must be some puny noble from the sticks.
Jahan: Wait a second. Even barbarians know that some things are just inappropriate for an occasion like this. Don't you agree?
Cecil: Ouch! Have mercy, Sir Jahan!

Jahan: What a rude little brat. Let me teach you a lesson! 
Hahaha...
Jahan: Ah, understood young master. I will not stay here and ruin the party mood. I'll go and take my place next to the door~
Royal Infantry Soldier: Sir Jahan. We have an emergency.
Jahan: What? Can't you see that I'm enjoying the party?
Royal Infantry Soldier: ...Yes, but Sir Dylan wants you to...
Jahan: Sir Dylan is looking for me!? Why didn't you say so? Let's go!
Jahan: The Vincent family...When I get the chance, you'll pay for humiliating me. Hmph.
